    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Walter Flavius McCaleb (1873-1967) was an American author of novels, plays, poetry, essays and 
	  non-fiction works regarding U.S. history.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Walter F. McCaleb Papers</emph> consists of material relating to his activities as an author 
	   of novels, plays, poetry, essays and non-fiction, with special 
	   emphasis on the Southwest, banking and finance in the U.S. and Mexico, and correspondence as an 
	   officer in the Brotherhood of Locomotive Engineers.  The collection contains autobiographical material, correspondence, writings (both published material and manuscripts), and memorabilia.</p><p><emph render="bold">Autobiographical material</emph> contains autobiographical and genealogical material, student papers, family correspondence.  Also included here are photographs, notes, and printed material relating to McCaleb's bicycle trip to Mexico in 1898.</p><p><emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> contains incoming and outgoing correspondence of a non-family nature; some deals with McCaleb's political and business concerns.  Correspondence relating to Franklin D. Roosevelt is foldered separately, as is McCaleb's correspondence with his publishers.</p><p><emph render="bold">Writings</emph> consists of manuscripts, typescripts, and typescript copies for books (both fiction and non-fiction), essays, plays, poetry, and short stories.  </p><p><emph render="bold">Memorabilia</emph> includes lists of McCaleb's library holdings, newsletters from the Aaron Burr Association, tax receipts, printed material, clippings, notebooks, and other assorted items.</p><p><emph render="bold">Published material</emph> contains books by McCaleb.</p>
    </scopecontent>
